# M1 — OpenAI-compatible translation (non-streaming)

**Date:** 2026-06-30
**Sprint label:** NEW
**Default labels:** enhancement, backend
**Status:** drafted

Milestone M1: add Mode B — translate the Anthropic Messages API to an
OpenAI-compatible Chat Completions backend and back — for a single,
env-selected upstream, **non-streaming and text-only**. This is the translation
core. Streaming is M2; tool calls (the make-or-break for real Claude Code use)
are M3; the full config.toml profile system and per-dispatch selection are M4.
Selection here is a tiny env switch (`CCPROXY_PROFILE`) so M4 can generalize it.
Depends on M0 (the passthrough path stays the `anthropic` profile, unchanged).

