## Notes

- **Env switch, not the full profile system.** M1 selection is just
  CCPROXY_PROFILE + OPENAI_BASE_URL / OPENAI_API_KEY / OPENAI_MODEL. Keep it
  minimal; M4 replaces it with config.toml profiles and per-dispatch resolution.
  Don't build the profile loader here.
- **Scope guard:** non-streaming + text only. Do NOT try to make Claude Code
  fully usable on the OpenAI path in this batch — that needs M2 (streaming) and
  M3 (tools). These tickets are the translation core only.
- **Order:** ticket 1 (schemas) → 2 (request) and 3 (response) → 4 (wire-up).
  Tickets 2 and 3 are independent of each other once schemas land.
- **Headless project.** Design Refs reference DESIGN.md "Intent"; UAT steps are
  `curl`/CLI based and MANUAL (no browser `[agent-test]` tags).
- **Test seam.** Stub the OpenAI upstream (monkeypatch httpx or a local ASGI app)
  so translation round-trips are deterministic and offline.
- **Optional reference:** teer823/claude-proxy `services/translator.py` and
  `schemas/` are a structural model — adapt, don't depend.

